defs.name: generate
defs.docs: Initializes a new `GenericArray` instance using the given function.

attributes.value: / Initializes a new `GenericArray` instance using the given function.
/ If the generator function panics while initializing the array,
/ any already initialized elements will be dropped.

defs.docs: Map a function over a slice to a `GenericArray`.

attributes.value: / Map a function over a slice to a `GenericArray`.
/ The length of the slice *must* be equal to the length of the array.

defs.name: map
defs.value: fn <U, F> (self, f: F) -> GenericArray<U, N>
defs.docs: Maps a `GenericArray` to another `GenericArray`.

attributes.value: / If the mapping function panics, any already initialized elements in the new array
/ will be dropped, AND any unused elements in the source array will also be dropped.

 initializing a new `GenericArray` with the result of the zipped mapping function.
